Siamese Network [same embedding network or encoder]
anchor -> embedd_net -> a
positive -> embedd_net -> p
negative -> embedd_net -> n

***********************************************************************************************************************************
Now Loss function  helps to a and p closer and making a and n apart, that how embedding space generated
Two loss function  for siamese network
1) Contrastive Pair loss
D : distance between pairs 
y is 0 if different pairs 1 if pairs are same.
L = (1-y)*D^2 + y.max(0, m-D)^2 

**************************************************************************************************************************************
2) Triple Margin loss
Distance between [Anchor and Positive] and  Distance between [Anchor and Negative] should have at least Margin distance

||F(A) - F(P)||^2 - ||F(A) - F(N)||^2 + alpha(margin) <=0   -> ||F(A) - F(P)||^2 + alpha(margin) - ||F(A) - F(N)||^2 <=0 

-> Loss(A,P,N) = MAX(||F(A) - F(P)||^2 + alpha(margin) - ||F(A) - F(N)||^2, 0) : Triplet Margin Loss
OR 
||F(A) - F(N)||^2 -||F(A) - F(P)||^2 <= alpha

